Reasoning: The paper discusses the measurement of collaboration patterns among academics, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories in computer science. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely category as the paper uses bibliometric analysis to measure collaboration patterns. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also likely as the paper examines the role of several variables in collaboration. cs.CY (Computers and Society) is another possible category as the paper discusses policies on academic career advancement. cs.SD (Software Engineering) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are less likely but still possible categories as the paper analyzes scientific production and the role of disciplines in collaboration.
